Read about "GitHub static page hosting" on https://pages.github.com/
Watch the complete tutorial - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZVejLE8qtOI
Create a new repository "testing-the-github-pages"
Create an "gh-pages" branch
Switch to & make it as default branch
https://github.com/your-username/repo/settings/branches
the "Default branch" section
Commit & push any file (text, image, or any other)
Check http://username.github.io/repository-name/
result: link to github.io shared file
